Job Description 
As an Electrical Maintenance Technician at Micron Technology, Inc., you will be responsible for ensuring uninterrupted supply of electrical service for the site. This is accomplished through continuous improvement and development of skills associated with the electrical trade. In this role, you will support the installation, removal, and repair oh high and low voltage equipment. Additional responsibilities include: serving as a resource for engineering and operations, domain expert for internal customers, and maintaining accurate maintenance records for proper tracking. 
Responsibilities and Tasks 
Maintain Site Electrical Utilities and Systems 
Maintain protective relays and transformers in substations 
Maintain motor control centers 
Maintain, repair, replace contactors, relays, timers, fuses, heaters, SAMMs, and soft starters 
Maintain, repair, replace a variety of UPS units 
Maintain medium voltage starters 
Perform IR scans of equipment as scheduled or requested 
Author and perform switching orders 
Support Safety, Environmental, Health, and Security Standards 
Achieve and maintain 100% completion of assigned EHSS training 
Maintain emergency power system (generators, automatic switches) 
Follow electric safe work practices 
Review equipment installs 
Perform safety analysis (Job Hazard Analysis) as the need arises 
Be proactive in reducing incidents of personal injury, safety hazards, or environmental releases 
Develop Technical Skills, Knowledge, and Abilities 
Participate in provided vendor training 
Learn, understand, and follow manufactures recommendation 
Author, review, and update procedures 
Maintain VA state electrical license 
Set up and operate electrical data capturing devices such as Dranetz or Square D Power Logic 
Manage and Monitor the Installation of New Equipment 
Support new equipment evaluation and qualification. 
Execute lock out tag out to de-energize equipment for safe working conditions 
Monitor installations for compliance to codes and standards 
Participate in Continuous Improvement and Reliability Initiatives 
Suggest and perform upgrade obsolete equipment 
Participate in focus groups with engineering and other disciplines 
Participate in Total Productive Maintenance program 
Analyze equipment performance to evaluate efficiencies 
Maintain Equipment and System Maintenance Records 
Complete data logs in Maximo and other applications used for tracking maintenance 
Create presentations via Microsoft Office applications 
Review and update records relative to assets 
Handle the inventory of all FOUPs 
Education 
Required 
Certificate 
1-year technical trades program 
Desired 
License 
Journeyman Electrical License -or- Equivalent Military training 
Additional Information: 
Additional Certifications: Medium Voltage certification; CPR/First aid certified 
